title: Dennis Brown - Money in My Pocket, The Definitive Collection (20
description:
Although he was only 42 when he died of respiratory problems in 1999, Dennis Brown had already enjoyed a three-decade
 career in Jamaican music, a career that saw him begin singing professionally at the age of nine, begin recording at 11,
 and score his first hit, "No Man Is an Island," at the age of 14. Before the final curtain fell, Brown recorded close
 to 100 albums and some 300 singles with various producers, making any attempt to chart his musical history a 
difficult one. The impressive two-disc Money in My Pocket collection does an admirable job, though, and quite wisely
 gives most of its space to Brown's creative peak in the mid- to late '70s and his work with Winston "Niney" Holness 
and Joe Gibbs, his two most consistently sympathetic producers.
